<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-05-13T05:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-13T05:30:00-05:00" n="726" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d726">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">856E.01/5–1347: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Batavia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Foote</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Batavia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-05-13T18:00:00+07:30">May 13,
                                    1947—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>175. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 119, May 2. Dept’s message
                            conveyed to <gloss target="#t_FEB1">FEB</gloss> Foreign Office on May 5.
                            Matter then emphasized to both Dutch and Sjahrir. British, Dutch and
                            Americans all anxious return at once to rehabilitate their properties.
                            Sjahrir agrees with every point in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> but he having mounting trouble with Communists and
                            radical labor organizations. For example, British personnel of one
                            British textile factory in east Java returned as technical advisers,
                            leaving management in hands <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> labor
                            union. Sjahrir hopeful can avoid such unfortunate actions in future and
                            promises try speed up implementation article 14. Dutch ready sign now
                            but <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>s unable agree among
                            themselves. Sjahrir promised advise me in near future.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Foote</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>